      "content": "I'm so sorry you're going through this; that sounds incredibly painful and exhausting. When nerve pain feels constant and overwhelming, it can make even the smallest movements feel impossible, and your body might feel like it's on fire or buzzing uncontrollably. It's completely understandable that you're feeling tired of fighting it, especially when your body feels like a cage of electricity.\n\nPlease know that this kind of pain is real, but it doesn't have to be permanent. While I can't offer medical advice, there are steps you can take to get support for this specific type of pain. Have you considered reaching out to a healthcare provider who specializes in chronic pain management? They might be able to adjust your treatment plan or suggest new therapies that could help break this cycle of constant discomfort.\n\nIn the meantime, small, gentle self-care practices might offer some relief. This could include trying relaxation techniques like deep breathing or guided meditation to help manage the stress that often worsens nerve pain, or seeking out a physical therapist who understands neuropathy. You don't have to face this alone, and there are people ready to help you find a way through this.",
