      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just the optimism that's the hardest part to deal with. everyone keeps saying \"try this\" or \"look for another way,\" but they aren't the ones living in it. they don't understand that for me, peace isn't something you find in a new pill or a therapist... it's just the absence of everything. it's the stillness. why is it so wrong to think that wanting to be done with the agony is just... a logical conclusion?",
